exclamation.description: Representing or suggesting a combination or rhythmic succession of clicking sounds. Often reduplicated.

noun.description: A combination or rhythmic succession of clicking sounds.
In bingo: (a nickname for) the number sixty-six.

verb.description: To make a rhythmic, swiftly paced succession or pattern of clicks.

origin: Early 19th century; earliest use found in Henry Cogswell Knight (1789–1835). From click + -ety + click.
